fields.description:
When the console is run behind an HTTPS-enabled reverse proxy such as nginx or Eucalyptus ELB, the messaging we provide when the secure cookie session session in the console.ini file is misconfigured (with 'session.secure = false'), we provide the following message, which doesn't clearly indicate how to fix the misconfigured setting...

{code}
HTTPS not detected. You will not be able to log in via HTTP unless the session.secure setting is properly configured. Please try again with a URL that begins with "https" instead of "http", and if the problem persists contact your cloud administrator.
{code}

We should provide inline comments in the console.ini file and/or supporting documentation on when the session.secure setting should be true.

UPDATE: Modified title to reflect that we're looking to provide a table/chart listing the config options (and what the defaults are) in the console.ini config file.  We should list the config values, flag which ones are required, and what the possible choices are for each config property.

comments.body:
[~dkavanagh]: If the file.uploads.enabled setting isn't in the console.ini, file_uploads_enabled defaults to True, looking at the following code…

{code}
self.file_uploads_enabled = asbool(self.request.registry.settings.get('file.uploads.enabled', True))
{code}

Note that pyramid.settings.asbool returns the value as-is if a boolean is passed, so we don't need to set the settings.get() default lookup to a string such as 'true'.  See http://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/pyramid/en/latest/api/settings.html#pyramid.settings.asbool
